
Overview of noun coat

The noun coat has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (29) coat -- (an outer garment that has sleeves and covers the body from shoulder down; worn outdoors)
2. (1) coating, coat -- (a thin layer covering something; "a second coat of paint")
3. coat, pelage -- (growth of hair or wool or fur covering the body of an animal)

Overview of verb coat

